fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.i18n.translators.yaml

Class YAMLTranslator

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.i18n.translators.Translator
      • fr.zcraft.quartzlib.components.i18n.translators.yaml.YAMLTranslator

  • public class YAMLTranslator
extends Translator
    Loads translations stored in a YAML file.
    • This translator does not support plurals. If plurals are used, the first string will always be used, and the other, ignored.
    • This translator does support contexts. The context is the superkey in the YAML structure (see below). Without context, the default one is keys.

    YAML structure

    The YAML structure must be this one:

         author: "The author name."
     team: "The translation team name. Defaults to the author if undefined."
     reports: "The contact to use to report translation errors. Defaults to the author if undefined."

     keys:
         greetings:
             hi: "Hi there"
             how: "How are you?"
     other_context:
         greetings:
             hi: "Hi!"
    With this structure, the keys are retrieved as follow: 
         I.t("greetings.hi")                       # Returns "Hi there"
     I.t("greetings.how")                      # Returns "How are you?"
     I.tc("other_context", "greetings.hi")    # Returns "Hi!"
